cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on improving the interpretability of deep neural networks for medical imaging, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of multiple instance learning (MIL) and bag-of-features models also suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the proposed method on histology datasets suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of logit heatmaps for interpretation suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
